Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_cell_binding(25.10)                                set_cell_binding(25.10)

Name
       set_cell_binding - Changes the layout binding for a cell

Syntax
       set_cell_binding

       [-help]

       [-abstract ]

       [-lib <list_of_libs>]

       -cell <list_of_cell_patterns>

       -view <list_of_views>

       Changes  the  layout  binding  for a cell. This also affects the layout
       viewing and automatic remastering. When specified with -abstract  para-
       meter,  this instead of affecting the abstract binding replaces the in-
       memory cell information with the matched cells.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each set_cell_binding parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man set_cell_binding.

       -abstract
              Replaces in-memory cell information for the matched cells.

       -cell <list_of_cell_patterns>
              Specifies  one  or  more  cell  name patterns that are to be re-
              placed.

       -lib <list_of_libs>
              Specifies the OpenAccess library that is to be used to look  for
              cell abstracts.

       -view <list_of_views>
              Specifies the cellview name.

Example
              * The following command looks for the cells in the Innovus data-
                base  that  match  the cell pattern and replaces their binding
                with the specified view found in the library list.

                set lib_list1 {lib1 lib2}

                set_cell_binding -lib $lib_list1  -cell  {cell1  cell2  cell3}
                -view {abc}

